Major health insurers in the U.S. are
reaping a third year of record profits as customers forgo or
postpone medical care amid a slowing economy, according to a New
York Times  report .  The UnitedHealth Group Inc. and  Cigna Corp. (CI)  reported low
level of medical use this year which signals the possibility of
a fundamental change in Americansâ€™ appetite for health care,
